title: Nasdaq Composite stands less than 1% from exiting correction territory Monday afternoon
text: The Nasdaq Composite Index on Monday afternoon was surging more than 3% higher, putting the technology-laden index within striking distance of exiting a plunge into correction territory produced back on Sept. 8. A drop of at least 10% for an asset from a recent peak is the commonly used definition on Wall Street for a correction, while putting in a new high after that decline is often viewed as that asset exiting that bearish phase of trading.
